snippet: Tuesday’s Republican victory ensures a new round of attention over the Affordable Care Act as people on both sides of the partisan divide would like to repair provisions of the law.
abstract: Republican victory in midterm elections ensures new round of political attacks on Affordable Care Act, but also creates potential opportunities to repair provisions of law that both Democrats and Republicans would like to fix.
lead_paragraph: Tuesday’s Republican victory ensures a new round of attention over the Affordable Care Act as people on both sides of the partisan divide would like to repair provisions of the law.
